{"id":221686,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacillus_subtilis","text":"\"Bacillus subtilis\" is an endospore-forming bacterium.\nIt is the source of the antibiotic bacitracin. \"Bacillus subtilis\" is a gram positive, rod-shaped bacterium. It is a facultative anaerobe commonly found in soil, and is also found in the gut flora.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Endospore","surface_form":"endospore","offset":26},{"uri":"Bacteria","surface_form":"bacterium","offset":44},{"uri":"Antibiotics","surface_form":"antibiotic","offset":79},{"uri":"Bacitracin","surface_form":"bacitracin","offset":90},{"uri":"Gram-positive","surface_form":"gram positive","offset":127},{"uri":"Facultative_anaerobe","surface_form":"facultative anaerobe","offset":172},{"uri":"Soil","surface_form":"soil","offset":211},{"uri":"Gut_flora","surface_form":"gut flora","offset":242}]}